channel.title: Videos
channel.description: Here’s what I’m pretty much known for. Videos of hacks that I’ve personally made! These are all on YouTube, but the raw file archive is available here.

item.title: Custom Sprite Insertion
item.description:
This was simply a test of custom sprite insertion into Heart gold and Soul silver, which was mildly successful.

Yes, it is Justin Bieber.

More to come.

item.title: Pokémon Black Introduction
item.description:
This was also alluded to previously with the initial hack that showed it was possible.

The process for hacking fifth gen is very similar to fourth, at least as far as text is concerned.

Fortunately text hacking is teh bestest. These games have still yet to come out in america, so once they do we’ll see what the community does as far as scripts and the like.

Most of this video was composed using pptxt, by SCV. It’s a very limited, but effective text editor. You can try this out yourself with the fifth gen download on the downloads page. The text .narcs for black and white are in a/0/0/2 and a/0/0/3. (2 contains elements like items and the intro while 3 continues much of the main story).

item.title: Better Rocket Uniform Patch
item.description:
Well, this is a little bit better. The advantages over the first one I did, besides being an actual downloadable patch, include a nice clean script interface, and also some fancy hexing footwork around some of the limitations of the uniform (i.e. inability to fly.) Unfortunately, as soon as I removed the inability, I found out why it was there in the first place– the Rocket Uniform is temporary and wares off when the character changes sprites.

I was pretty disappointed when I found this out, but the event is rather nice and clean and I had already put the effort into it so I’m sharing it anyway.

To perfect his hack, short of modifying every single revert to original sprites check if the Rocket Uniform is on, would probably require an item. That way if the uniform were removed it could be put back on instantly. Also using the phone could work. I don’t have HEX offsets for either of those... however... so...

Well, darn. Maybe later.

item.title: Impromptu Rocket Uniform Implementation
item.description:
Wow, those are a lot of big words. Anyway, this is just a jerry-rigged version of an option to take on and off the Rocket uniform controlled by the player.

When I was playing through this games, i wondered why this wasn’t an option and the idea for this immediately came to me.

I’d like to see it on some item, as I don’t know about the side-effects it has with the story, so we’ll see.

Patch coming soon, regardless of the side-effects, most likely.

item.title: Limping into Fourth Gen
item.description:
What was first just a mistake in laying down the sprites in Soul Silver, I decided to record and make this video.

It looks like the character is “limping” into fourth gen, kind of like Duster from Mother 3.

I’ve since fixed this, but it has stirred my brain for an Earthbound crossover...

I mean, what?

item.title: Pokémon Black Hack
item.description: Just testing the waters. As you can see, I did mess up, but the process is remarkably similar to fourth gen, so you can expect progress to carry over as soon as they are released in America.

item.title: Pokémon Soul Silver Introduction
item.description:
This is it! The start of fourth generation hacking! After much work I have finally figured out how to edit text in it... It was kind of complicated too.

Maybe I’ll get a tutorial up soon, but I don’t know.

The actual content of this video is pretty much you’d expect from an introduction hack. The two screens do pan when necessary, although I can’t imagine that will be required in areas that aren’t The Intro.

Map editing coming soon? No clue, but perhaps Black and White if the process is similar enough...

item.title: Play as Gym Leader in FireRed
item.description:
This video is a good one! You should be sure to watch all of it!

But seriously, I had the idea for this and I just couldn’t resist. It’s kind of completely true once you think about it...

There is actually a little bit of hacking involved here– about one or two minutes into the video the antagonist tries to move but finds that he is unable to.

Lol?

item.title: Ash Goes To Unova!
item.description:
This is a good one! Written almost entirely by whatsherface, with the exception of myself who chose to incorporate Bill in on the shenanigans along with the secret garden.

Unova is the new region in case you haven’t heard already. It was just announced today!

item.title: S.S. Anne Team Rocket Event!
item.description: This is a cool video, I promise. I was going for sort of a sense of “realism” here. Does that even mean anything in this “field?” Probably not, but like, I think it’s really cool, so you should too. Unfortunately, during the battle Ash’s PIkachu actually gets defeated by a Wobbuffet... but oh well. Another thing, Escape Ropes don’t actually work in this area... so I had to modify them to be able to. One last little bonus: there actually is an item where Ash’s Pikachu is found. It’s a Lava Cookie. You can get it by trading to get HM05 Flash instead of getting it from the Captain, and then returning later in the game when you have HM04 Surf.

item.title: Why RED Can't Talk in HG/SS
item.description: Now, I don’t know about this one. It’s something entirely different but also something that I’ve been wanting to try for a while. Benv20 contacted me about doing some sort of collab, and he offered me his voice, which I so eagerly accepted. I hope the joke comes across. Also, I’m so silly, for I removed the background music instead of lowering it. And another thing, I don’t even think that the title makes sense! I mean, it might. Also, he isn’t a Voice Actor if it’s just himself. That’s silly. Benv20 is the Voice Actor, RED is the character...

item.title: New Eevee Types in Pokémon Emerald!
item.description: This is another cool one! The idea is that science is wrong, or something. This one also has that sort of “realistic” tone to it. The sprites were hard to get in though... The Robo-Eevee one was more customly made, but the Ghost-Eevee was pretty much completely stolen from somebody through Google Images... OH WELL. This one should send shivers down your spine... and if it doesn’t, well, too bad. ALSO THE IDEA FOR THE HACK WAS STOLEN FROM THE GIRL. Whatever that means. Also, please notice that the Robo-Eevee has no nature, and that the ghost Eevee has the same nature as the one that “died.”

item.title: From a Realistic Perspective...
item.description: Okay, this involves fighting Team Rocket under realistic conditions. I mean, they’re like a mafia and stuff or something, so they just totally would kill you and your pathetic Pokémon. Then again, I think a Pokémon would realistically just trump a gun... but... oh well, it’s funny! I hope... Enjoy!

item.title: Pokémon Emerald: Multiplayer Style
item.description:
I don’t have many vids that make people go liek OMFG THAT IS AMAZING. But if anything would do it, it’s this one. Multiplayer is something that people have been dying to see in the games, and here’s what it would look like!

This actually has four VBAs linked to each other, two set to arrow keys and the other two set to WASD controls. It’s pretty cool!
